CBRE are pleased to offer 118 Regent Street Redfern to the market for sale via an Auction campaign.

Main features include;

- Zoned B4 mixed use
- Zoning allows for:
  Education, Community, Commercial or Residential, Bars,
  Cafes, Restaurants, Childcare, Medical

The property will be sold by on-site Auction on Wednesday 6th September 2017 at 11.30am

If you wish to obtain further information, please contact the listing agents:

Peter Vines – 0449 857 100
Stephen Grant – 0422 825 280

CBRE, as the exclusive selling agent, is pleased to present 167 Regent Street, Redfern. This mixed use building is situated in a rapidly gentrifying suburb and comprises a bridal dress shop and two bedroom apartment. The property is within 250m* of Redfern Train Station and the new Australian Technology Park which is expected to cater for 18,000 workers in the coming years.

Key investment highlights of 167 Regent Street, Redfern include:


- City fringe mixed use investment
- Retail shop plus a two-bedroom shop top apartment
- Ground floor retail on 3 + 3 year lease
- Net income of $50,001 per annum*
- 250m* from Redfern Train Station
- Within 500m* of the Australian Technology Park and future Waterloo Metro Station
- Situated in a high traffic commercial precinct well positioned for growth

167 Regent Street, Redfern will be sold via public auction on Tuesday, 9 April at 10.30am.

For further information, please contact the exclusive CBRE selling agents.

Situated at 7-9 Gibbons St, Redfern, literally across the road from Redfern Train Station and the new South Eveleigh (previously Australian Technology Park), this location cannot be beaten.

A smart and contemporary office space with multiple meeting rooms/offices, boardroom, kitchen/breakout and open plan working area, this is a great opportunity for those seeking a ready to occupy suite in a favourable location.

In close proximity to a supermarket, cafes/restaurants/bars, health/medical centre, fitness facilities and more.

Features:
• Approximately 157sqm with a 49sqm additional balcony
• Soaring ceilings creating a space of massive volume
• Polished concrete flooring
• A mixture of fitted out and open plan working area
• Equipped with a full kitchen
• Fibre optic cabling / NBN ready
• Plethora of F&B operators at your doorstep
• Full DDA compliance (ambulant and wheelchair facilities and access)
• Secure basement parking – plenty available
• 50 metres from Redfern Train Station
• Within walking distance of the Sydney CBD, the Universities (UTS/UNSW/USyd/Notre Dame) and Central Station

For more information or to arrange an inspection, feel free to reach out to the CBRE agents below:

Fergus Bowen – 0416 538 727, Fergus.bowen@cbre.com
Brendan Shipp – 0421 714 362, Brendan.shipp@cbre.com.au

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: FITTED OUT AND MODERN CREATIVE OFFICE DIRECTLY ACROSS FROM REDFERN TRAIN STATION

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Perfectly positioned between George and Pitt Streets, this landmark 2 level commercial building will suit a multitude of uses. The total NLA over both floors is 1,571sqm with potential to convert this unpolished gem into a company headquarters with plenty of parking, and increase the NLA dramatically (STCA).

The current configuration is a large clear span warehouse area on the ground floor ideal for abundant parking or refurbishment into creative office space. The first floor / mezzanine office is accessible via 2 flights of stairs at the front and rear of the building or via a passenger lift.

A rooftop garden area with views to the city and South to the Airport is a nice surprise.

This building is ideally located, an easy 1 minute walk to the revitalised Redfern Park  and the new South Sydney Rabbitohs training ground & refurbished leagues club.  Redfern train station is a 3 minute walk away.  Be amongst the new art galleries, cafes and work studios that are now pushing into the area.

Capitalise now and purchase a landmark building in the fastest growing City Fringe location. Then benefit in the future from the many large media companies like Channel 7 that are moving into the local area, and all the smaller associated companies that will need to be close by these large local tenants.

All this within a 5 minute drive to the CBD and 10 minutes to the Airport, with easy access to all the main arterial roads (Cross City Tunnel, Harbour Bridge and Tunnel and Anzac Bridge).

FSR: 2:1
Zoning: "3 Business"

An Inspection of this building is a must.
